---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-to-look-for', text: 'What to Look For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-considerations', text: 'Coverage Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'destination-matters', text: 'Destination Matters', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Couples Insurance', href: '/best/couples-insurance' },
  { title: 'Mental Health Insurance', href: '/best/mental-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Premium Insurance', href: '/best/premium-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'samePartner', header: 'Same-Sex Partners' },
  { key: 'transHealth', header: 'Trans Healthcare' },
  { key: 'mentalHealth', header: 'Mental Health' },
  { key: 'hiv', header: 'HIV/PrEP' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', samePartner: 'Full coverage', transHealth: 'Varies by plan', mentalHealth: 'Comprehensive', hiv: 'Covered' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', samePartner: 'Full coverage', transHealth: 'Varies by plan', mentalHealth: 'Comprehensive', hiv: 'Covered' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', samePartner: 'Full coverage', transHealth: 'Limited', mentalHealth: 'Good', hiv: 'Covered' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', samePartner: 'Full coverage', transHealth: 'Limited', mentalHealth: 'Good', hiv: 'Covered' },
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', samePartner: 'Full coverage', transHealth: 'Not covered', mentalHealth: 'Limited', hiv: 'Emergency only' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best LGBTQ+ Friendly Expat Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance that covers same-sex partners, transgender healthcare, and LGBTQ+ specific needs. Find inclusive coverage for living abroad."
  headline="Best LGBTQ+ Friendly Expat Insurance"
  subheadline="Finding inclusive international health insurance matters. Here are the insurers that cover same-sex partners, offer transgender healthcare, and provide comprehensive mental health support."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-lgbtq-friendly-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top LGBTQ+ Friendly Picks</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the most inclusive coverage for LGBTQ+ expats:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🏳️‍🌈</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Overall LGBTQ+ Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Full same-sex partner coverage, strong mental health, HIV/PrEP covered. Corporate diversity commitment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">👑</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Premium Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Comprehensive coverage including partners, excellent mental health, inclusive policies.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💚</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Mental Health Focus</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Comprehensive mental health with telemedicine. Important for LGBTQ+ individuals facing discrimination abroad.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💰</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Budget Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Basic coverage at $45/month. Covers partners equally. Limited on specialized care.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-to-look-for">What to Look For</h2>
  <p>
    LGBTQ+ friendly international health insurance should include:
  </p>

  <h3>Same-Sex Partner Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Most major international insurers now cover same-sex partners:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Spouse/partner coverage regardless of gender</li>
    <li>No marriage requirement (domestic partnership accepted)</li>
    <li>Same benefits as opposite-sex couples</li>
    <li>Family plans that include same-sex parents</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Transgender Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage varies significantly:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Hormone therapy (HRT) - sometimes covered</li>
    <li>Gender-affirming surgery - rarely covered</li>
    <li>Mental health support - usually covered</li>
    <li>Routine care - always covered regardless of gender identity</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Important:</strong> Most international health plans exclude gender-affirming surgeries as "elective." Some cover hormone therapy; others don't. Always verify specific coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Mental Health Support</h3>
  <p>
    Critical for LGBTQ+ individuals, especially those in less accepting countries:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Therapy and counseling coverage</li>
    <li>Telemedicine mental health (access from anywhere)</li>
    <li>LGBTQ+ affirming therapists in network</li>
    <li>No low session limits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>HIV/AIDS Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Look for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>PrEP coverage (prevention)</li>
    <li>HIV treatment if positive</li>
    <li>Regular testing covered</li>
    <li>No discriminatory exclusions</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Find Inclusive Coverage"
    description="Compare LGBTQ+ friendly international health insurance options."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">LGBTQ+ Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
    * Coverage details vary by specific plan. Transgender healthcare coverage is evolving—verify current terms directly with insurers.
  </p>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Overall LGBTQ+ Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna has strong corporate diversity commitments that extend to their international health products.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full same-sex partner/spouse coverage</li>
    <li>Comprehensive mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Telemedicine for mental health anywhere</li>
    <li>HIV/PrEP coverage</li>
    <li>No discriminatory exclusions</li>
    <li>Corporate diversity track record</li>
    <li>LGBTQ+ friendly customer service training</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Gender-affirming surgery typically excluded. Hormone therapy coverage varies by plan. Premium pricing.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Premium Option</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers comprehensive coverage with inclusive policies.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Same-sex partner coverage</li>
    <li>Excellent mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Premium service and support</li>
    <li>HIV coverage</li>
    <li>Global network access</li>
    <li>Inclusive approach to coverage</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Most expensive option. Gender-affirming surgery typically excluded. Best if you need premium coverage anyway.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>SafetyWing — Budget LGBTQ+ Option</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing covers same-sex partners equally at their low price point.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Same-sex partners covered equally</li>
    <li>Low cost ($45/month)</li>
    <li>No discrimination in coverage</li>
    <li>Easy enrollment</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Limited mental health coverage. No transgender-specific healthcare. HIV covered only for emergencies (pre-existing excluded). Travel medical only, not full health insurance.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/safetywing">Read our full SafetyWing review</a></p>

  <h2 id="coverage-considerations">Coverage Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Transgender Healthcare Reality</h3>
  <p>
    The reality of transgender healthcare coverage in international health insurance:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Gender-affirming surgery:</strong> Almost universally excluded as "cosmetic" or "elective"</li>
    <li><strong>Hormone therapy:</strong> Sometimes covered, often excluded—verify carefully</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Usually covered, including gender dysphoria treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Routine care:</strong> Covered regardless of gender identity</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If you need gender-affirming care, you may need to plan for out-of-pocket costs or seek coverage in specific countries with better regulations.
  </p>

  <h3>HIV/AIDS Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>New diagnosis while insured:</strong> Typically covered like any new condition</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing HIV:</strong> May face exclusions or higher premiums</li>
    <li><strong>PrEP:</strong> Increasingly covered by major insurers</li>
    <li><strong>Medication access:</strong> May vary by country—check local availability</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mental Health Access</h3>
  <p>
    For LGBTQ+ expats, mental health access is often crucial:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Living in less accepting countries can be isolating</li>
    <li>Telemedicine allows access to LGBTQ+ affirming therapists</li>
    <li>Look for plans without low session limits</li>
    <li>Verify therapists in your language are available</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Mental Health Matters"
    description="Choose plans with comprehensive mental health coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="destination-matters">Destination Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Where you live affects your healthcare experience as an LGBTQ+ person:
  </p>

  <h3>LGBTQ+ Friendly Destinations</h3>
  <p>
    Countries with good LGBTQ+ healthcare access:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Western Europe:</strong> Spain, Netherlands, Germany, Portugal</li>
    <li><strong>North America:</strong> Canada, parts of US</li>
    <li><strong>South America:</strong> Argentina, Uruguay, parts of Brazil</li>
    <li><strong>Asia-Pacific:</strong> Thailand, Taiwan, parts of Australia</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Challenging Destinations</h3>
  <p>
    Countries where LGBTQ+ healthcare may be difficult:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Countries where homosexuality is illegal</li>
    <li>Regions with limited LGBTQ+ aware providers</li>
    <li>Areas with significant discrimination</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    In these locations, telemedicine mental health and the ability to travel for care become more important.
  </p>

  <h3>Insurance Still Works Everywhere</h3>
  <p>
    Even in challenging destinations:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your insurance covers medical care regardless of local laws</li>
    <li>You can use telemedicine for sensitive consultations</li>
    <li>Evacuation coverage lets you travel for specialized care</li>
    <li>International insurers don't discriminate based on local country attitudes</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Will my same-sex partner be covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, with all major international health insurers. Cigna, Bupa, Aetna, Allianz, and others cover same-sex partners/spouses with the same benefits as opposite-sex couples. Most don't require legal marriage—domestic partnership is usually sufficient.
  </p>

  <h3>Is hormone therapy (HRT) covered?</h3>
  <p>
    It varies. Some plans cover hormone therapy as part of mental health or endocrine treatment. Others exclude it. You must verify with each insurer before purchasing. Get it in writing.
  </p>

  <h3>What about gender-affirming surgery?</h3>
  <p>
    Almost universally excluded from international health insurance as "elective" or "cosmetic." This is an industry-wide limitation. You'll likely need to pay out-of-pocket or seek care in countries where public systems cover it.
  </p>

  <h3>Is PrEP covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Increasingly yes with major insurers like Cigna and Bupa. It's considered preventive care. Verify with your specific plan and check medication availability in your destination country.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I access LGBTQ+ affirming therapists?</h3>
  <p>
    Through telemedicine, yes. Premium insurers offer mental health telemedicine with access to therapists who understand LGBTQ+ issues. This is valuable even in countries with limited local LGBTQ+ affirming providers.
  </p>

  <h3>Will my insurance work in countries where being LGBTQ+ is illegal?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. International health insurance operates independently of local laws regarding sexual orientation. Your coverage remains valid. However, local healthcare providers may have discriminatory attitudes—telemedicine and evacuation coverage provide alternatives.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Coverage for transgender healthcare and LGBTQ+ specific needs varies significantly and is evolving. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify current coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
